      "writtenOn": "2018-12-03T18:49:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "they still do because graph.add_node is global, isn\u0027t it?\n\nalso it is bit weird that users are expected to call global key() and non-global node().\nI am not sure this complexity is justified. I think it would be simpler to have just one graph object that freezes after script runs.",
