    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "7532c14e_de6e2511",
        "filename": "lucicfg/genctx.go",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 54,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002539
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-12-03T23:31:33Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Fine, removed this, everything happens through global \u0027graph\u0027 now.\n\nThe original idea was to limit visibility of various mutating APIs only to callbacks that do the mutation. There are two such mutating APIs: building graph and generating configs.\n\nSo originally I planned to have something like this (cargoculting Bazel\u0027s \u0027rule\u0027):\n\ndef _trigger(ctx):\n  ctx.graph.add_node(...)\n  for b in ctx.attrs.triggers:\n    ctx.graph.add_edge(...)\n\ntrigger \u003d node(\n    impl \u003d _trigger,\n    attrs \u003d {\n        \u0027repo\u0027: attr.string(),\n        \u0027triggers\u0027: [attr.string()],\n    }\n)\n\n\nHere graph-mutation stuff is accessible only through \u0027ctx\u0027 which is \"node declaration context\".\n\nAnother context is \"generator context\". It has APIs to traverse the graph and emit configs, but not to define any new nodes.\n\nThen I decided node(...) thing is probably an overkill for now. But I wanted to simplify future change to use context-scoped APIs. That\u0027s how generator context got ctx.graph.node(...).\n\nBut this is not important, and can be changed in the future.",
      "parentUuid": "49a65d25_04fa4105",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 53,
        "startChar": 2,
        "endLine": 54,
        "endChar": 43
      },
      "revId": "74da84ae6ac9db5530beb4f21c13bf9f91f3620f",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
