    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "fd0a7c3f_e4804a12",
        "filename": "lucicfg/graph/graph.go",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 85,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002539
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-12-03T23:31:33Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e if we make it a struct in the end, why don\u0027t we accept struct from users?\n\nBecause constructing structs looks a bit awkward from starlark side, and strictly speaking structs are not part of core starlark.\n\n\u003e it is weird to add props are dict, but read it as struct.\n\nI disagree.\n\n\u003e then we wouldn\u0027t need to do L72 check\n\u003e \n\u003e if we don\u0027t intend to add more node attrs to node besides key and trace, maybe we could even do\n\u003e   \n\u003e   graph.node(key\u003dgraph.key(\u0027a\u0027, \u0027b\u0027), foo\u003d\u0027c\u0027, bar\u003d\u0027c\u0027)\n\u003e \n\u003e it works fine in ndb. Having a property named \"key\" would be confusing\n\nI don\u0027t like this, it mixes two different namespaces into one. Also it is more difficult to visually see what exactly is being available as .props (they are no longer grouped together).",
      "parentUuid": "acb45398_6532da44",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 85,
        "startChar": 9,
